&nbsp;
"As for every human instrument - it has emphasized however Mantovano - the AI presents a dark side: contains seeds of every species and germs of every life. Among the most dangerous seeds are the injury of confidentiality, the new forms of digital vulnerability, the opening of laundering, creation and propagation fake news>. In this regard, the conceptual IA does not bring anything new to the disinformation of totalitarian regimes, > but it can increase the potential offensive, affecting the process of manifestation of democratic freedom. The subject of the proportion of controls is therefore central." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
For Mantovano, therefore, "it is crucial to identify shared ethical and judicial criteria both for the use of AI and to determine precepts and sanctions for those who disconnect. In short - he has remembered - the Council of Ministers will design a bill with the principles to which the use of AI must be inspired, counting the potential and controls necessary to program the algorithms".
&nbsp;
Another "fundamental voice", he added, "is the progressive dehumanization of society > and law, and that is why the supervision of man must continue to be central: Democracy cannot be technocracy, the right cannot be reduced to the application of algorithms" and "the lawyers must be on the front line to ensure that AI is placed at the service of the best use of rights, that protect the public interest without orwellian twists. The tool will change the forensic profession, you will lose functions that were customary, what should not change - the undersecretary has concluded - is the role of sentinel that lawyers will continue to perform". &nbsp;
